<p><b>What is the power of faith by Bishop David Oyedepo?</b> The Supernatural Power of Faith by Bishop David Oyedepo. What is Faith? Faith is obeying God to prove that we believe him thereby committing him to commit to his word and to make good of his promises (Genesis 12:4). Faith is not a believe system, it is an active spiritual force.</p>
<p><b>What is divine wisdom by David Oyedepo?</b> But, what is Divine Wisdom? Divine wisdom is trading the truth of the Word of God for the supernatural triumph we desire in life. Jesus once said: Therefore whosoever heareth these sayings of mine, and doeth them, I will liken him unto a wise man… (Matthew 7:24-25).</p>
<p><b>What is Bishop David Oyedepo mission statement?</b> We are an arm of the Living Faith Church Worldwide. Our vision, as delivered to the Presiding Bishop, Dr David Oyedepo, is to preach the Word of Faith, liberating men everywhere from every oppression of the devil.</p>
<p><b>What is the unlimited power of faith?</b> The Unlimited Power of Faith is a powerful testimony to what faith in God can accomplish and what we have so carelessly overlooked. Religion has blinded us into living a life of mediocrity as opposed to how God has prepared for us to live just based on having simple faith...</p>
<p><b>How to access divine guidance by Bishop David Oyedepo?</b> </p>
<p><b>What are the 4 types of wisdom?</b> “There are four classes of wisdom, according to James 3:15-17: earthly wisdom, intellectual wisdom, devilish wisdom and the wisdom from above,” he explained. He elucidated that earthly wisdom was the same as common sense; for instance, the instinct told a newborn baby where the mother's breast was situated.</p>
<p><b>What are the 7 types of wisdom?</b> Wisdom's seven pillars, according to scripture, are: fear of the Lord, instruction, knowledge, understanding, discretion, counsel, and reproof.</p>
<p><b>What is the power of faith?</b> Simply put, faith is a strong belief or trust in something or someone beyond oneself. This can be a higher power, spiritual strength, or even a sense of purpose. Despite its subjective nature, faith is prevalent throughout the world and can bring great comfort and hope to those who possess it.</p>
<p><b>What is the power of true faith?</b> “Now faith is the assurance of things hoped for, the conviction of things not seen. For by it the people of old received their commendation. By faith we understand that the universe was created by the word of God, so that what is seen was not made out of things that are visible.”</p>
<p><b>What is the power of living by faith?</b> Living by faith means any power to persevere for Christ only comes from seeing the perseverance of Christ. His endurance to carry his heavy Cross for me gives me the desire to carry my light and momentary cross for him (Heb. 12:1-3, Luke 9:23).</p>
<p><b>What is power of words by Bishop Oyedepo?</b> Your words are forces of deliverance, so sow the right words. ➡Your Words Commit God. God is committed to perform whatever you release from your mouth; and when God is committed, no devil can resist Him. God has nothing to act upon, until you have uttered a word.</p>